David,

Thank your very much for your prompt answer. 
Unfortunately, trying to build the solution Cantera.sln which I 
downloaded from the CVS repository I got the following linker error 
(together with others but they are of minor importance and can be 
easily corrected):

clib fatal error LNK1181: cannot open input file &#39;cvode.lib&#39;

I could not find a project in this solution, which generates this 
library. Probably, I am doing very silly mistake but it seems that 
this solution is quite different than that in the latest source 
distribution.

Are all the projects before submitting to the CVS repositoryin have 
been checked that they can be built ? Or it is much better do not 
touch the CVS repository and build Cantera from the latest source 
distribution?

Best regards, 
Anatoli Mokhov




